    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "Systematic h-refinement mesh convergence study performed on the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated for construct stiffness and von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the discretization error at the fine mesh level. The study concluded that the fine mesh (approximately 420 000 elements) achieves a grid convergence index below 1.2% for all quantities of interest, satisfying the ASME V&V 10.1 criterion.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
